#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.hypergeometric.rst:4
msgid "numpy.random.Generator.hypergeometric"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/random/generated/numpy.random.Generator.hypergeometric.rst:8
msgid "method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:2
msgid "Draw samples from a Hypergeometric distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:4
msgid ""
"Samples are drawn from a hypergeometric distribution with specified "
"parameters, `ngood` (ways to make a good selection), `nbad` (ways to make a "
"bad selection), and `nsample` (number of items sampled, which is less than "
"or equal to the sum ``ngood + nbad``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:13
msgid "**ngood**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:-1
msgid "int or array_like of ints"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:12
msgid ""
"Number of ways to make a good selection.  Must be nonnegative and less than "
"10**9."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:17
msgid "**nbad**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:16
msgid ""
"Number of ways to make a bad selection.  Must be nonnegative and less than "
"10**9."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:21
msgid "**nsample**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:20
msgid ""
"Number of items sampled.  Must be nonnegative and less than ``ngood + nbad``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:30
msgid "**size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:-1
msgid "int or tuple of ints, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:24
msgid ""
"Output shape.  If the given shape is, e.g., ``(m, n, k)``, then ``m * n * "
"k`` samples are drawn.  If size is ``None`` (default), a single value is "
"returned if `ngood`, `nbad`, and `nsample` are all scalars.  Otherwise, ``np."
"broadcast(ngood, nbad, nsample).size`` samples are drawn."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:0
msgid "Returns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:43
msgid "**out**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:-1
msgid "ndarray or scalar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:35
msgid ""
"Drawn samples from the parameterized hypergeometric distribution. Each "
"sample is the number of good items within a randomly selected subset of size "
"`nsample` taken from a set of `ngood` good items and `nbad` bad items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:48
msgid ":obj:`multivariate_hypergeometric`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:49
msgid "Draw samples from the multivariate hypergeometric distribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:50
msgid ":obj:`scipy.stats.hypergeom`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:51
msgid ""
"probability density function, distribution or cumulative density function, "
"etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:55
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:56
msgid ""
"The probability mass function (PMF) for the Hypergeometric distribution is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:58
msgid ""
"P(x) = \\frac{\\binom{g}{x}\\binom{b}{n-x}}{\\binom{g+b}{n}},\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:60
msgid "where :math:`0 \\le x \\le n` and :math:`n-b \\le x \\le g`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:62
msgid ""
"for P(x) the probability of ``x`` good results in the drawn sample, g = "
"`ngood`, b = `nbad`, and n = `nsample`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:65
msgid ""
"Consider an urn with black and white marbles in it, `ngood` of them are "
"black and `nbad` are white. If you draw `nsample` balls without replacement, "
"then the hypergeometric distribution describes the distribution of black "
"balls in the drawn sample."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:70
msgid ""
"Note that this distribution is very similar to the binomial distribution, "
"except that in this case, samples are drawn without replacement, whereas in "
"the Binomial case samples are drawn with replacement (or the sample space is "
"infinite). As the sample space becomes large, this distribution approaches "
"the binomial."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:76
msgid ""
"The arguments `ngood` and `nbad` each must be less than `10**9`. For "
"extremely large arguments, the algorithm that is used to compute the samples "
"[R688e4aa3bfc3-4]_ breaks down because of loss of precision in floating "
"point calculations.  For such large values, if `nsample` is not also large, "
"the distribution can be approximated with the binomial distribution, "
"`binomial(n=nsample, p=ngood/(ngood + nbad))`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:84
msgid "References"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:85
msgid ""
"Lentner, Marvin, \"Elementary Applied Statistics\", Bogden and Quigley, 1972."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:87
msgid ""
"Weisstein, Eric W. \"Hypergeometric Distribution.\" From MathWorld--A "
"Wolfram Web Resource. https://mathworld.wolfram.com/"
"HypergeometricDistribution.html"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:90
msgid ""
"Wikipedia, \"Hypergeometric distribution\", https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Hypergeometric_distribution"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:92
msgid ""
"Stadlober, Ernst, \"The ratio of uniforms approach for generating discrete "
"random variates\", Journal of Computational and Applied Mathematics, 31, pp. "
"181-189 (1990)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._generator.Generator.hypergeometric:98
msgid ""
